Introducing the latest addition to the Marvel Bishoujo series: Rogue from the X-Men! This stunning 1:7 scale figure captures Rogue in her adorable retro 90's outfit and hairstyle, bringing back a wave of nostalgia. Designed by the talented artist Shunya Yamashita, this figure focuses on Rogue's evolved power to absorb and control multiple mutant abilities simultaneously.
Unlike a mere reimagining of the original figure, this design offers a fresh take on Rogue, featuring a never-before-seen expression and a playful twist by incorporating the powers of other X-Men characters. One striking addition is the bone claws, absorbed from the popular X-Men member Wolverine, known for his healing abilities and retractable claws. Rogue stands proudly atop a base crafted to resemble ice, representing the cryokinetic powers she absorbed from Iceman. Additionally, scattered at her feet are cards imbued with Gambit's molecular acceleration, granting her the ability to manipulate kinetic energy.
The sculptor behind this exceptional figure is Takaboku Busujima (BUSUJIMAX), whose masterful craftsmanship brings together the various elements that unmistakably identify Rogue as a member of the X-Men. Made from high-quality PVC, this figure stands approximately 9 inches tall, making it a captivating addition to your collection.
 
Don't miss out on adding this powerful superheroine with incredible, unseen potential to your collection. The Marvel Bishoujo Rogue 1:7 Scale Figure beautifully captures the essence of the character and pays homage to the beloved X-Men series. Whether you're a fan of Rogue or a collector of Marvel memorabilia, this figure is a must-have. Get ready to showcase Rogue's dynamic abilities and relive the magic of the 90s with this exceptional piece.
Proudly brought to you by Kotobukiya and Superhero Toystore, India's largest and most comprehensive online store for official Marvel Action Figures, Statues, and other Pop-culture merch!

title: Transformers: Dark of the Moon (Film) Sideswipe DX Bonus Version Statue by Prime 1 Studio
description:
Prime 1 Studio is thrilled to introduce another elite Autobot in our Museum Masterline Series: the Non-Scale Sideswipe Deluxe Bonus Version from Transformers: Dark of the Moon!
Sideswipe, known for his incredible speed and agility on both four wheels and two, is a master of ranged weaponry and prefers engaging his enemies with double-sword melee attacks!
In Transformers: Dark of the Moon, Sideswipe played a crucial role, assisting Bumblebee in the takeover of an illegal power plant in the Middle East, fighting alongside Ironhide against Sentinel Prime, and surviving the explosion of the Xantium with his fellow Autobots.
This 22-inch statue showcases Sideswipe's sleek silver metallic armor, intricately sculpted with detailed machinery, plating, and electronics that mimic the real thing. With his arm cannons at the ready, Sideswipe appears alert and vibrant, with light-up eyes and chest lights powered by LEDs. The Deluxe Bonus Version also includes Sideswipe's signature arm-mounted Cybertanium swords, adding an extra level of authenticity to this collectible.
Balancing effortlessly on his twin-wheeled form, Sideswipe stands prepared for any confrontation on a meticulously designed Autobots base featuring the prominent Autobots logo front and center.
As a bonus for this version, we are offering Transformers Logo Plates that can be displayed alongside your Sideswipe statue. The Global Bonus Version includes the Transformers logo in English, while the Chinese Bonus Version features the Chinese version of the Transformers Logo Plate.

Proudly brought to you by Prime 1 Studios and Superhero Toystore, India's largest and most comprehensive online store for Transformers Action Figures, Statues, and other Pop culture Merchandise!

title: Dark Nights: Death Metal (Comics) Superman Deluxe Version Statue by Prime 1 Studio
description:
Prime 1 Studio proudly presents the epic 1:3 Scale Death Metal Superman Deluxe Version from Dark Nights: Death Metal, joining our Museum Masterline collection!
Dark Nights: Death Metal, the culmination of the Dark Multiverse Saga by Scott Snyder, Greg Capullo, and Jonathan Glapion, unites multiple storylines into a single universe. In this thrilling installment, the Batman Who Laughs holds our heroes captive, and Wonder Woman embarks on a daring mission to rescue Superman from Darkfather's clutches. What emerges is a long-haired, Darkseid-infected Superman, wielding his guitar with lightning-fast fingers, ready to unleash an apocalyptic guitar solo.
Prime 1 Studio presents a unique rendition of the Man of Steel, forever changed by the Anti-Life Equation and tortured by Darkfather's Murder Machine. Standing at a towering height of over 37 inches, this Superman exudes ultimate rage as he fights his final battle to save humanity. His flowing long hair adds to his majestic appearance, while the Darkseid infection visibly manifests in his powerful, rock-like right arm. The ripped shirt, leather trousers, steel belt, and crimson boots form the perfect heavy metal outfit befitting the one and only Kal-El. At his feet, the Darkest Knight and Perpetua's demonic horde reach out amidst obsidian razor-sharp stones, symbolizing the depths of the abyss. And anchoring it all is the S-Shield, the emblem of hope from Krypton.
The Death Metal Superman Deluxe Version offers even more metal madness. It includes two additional heads with different expressions, allowing you to choose between an angry or stern look, screaming or teeth clenched. With the two included display headstands, you can showcase your Death Metal Superman with the utmost metal style.
 
Proudly brought to you by Prime 1 Studios and Superhero Toystore, India's largest and most comprehensive online store for official DC Comics Superman Action Figures, Statues, and other Pop-culture merch!

title: Spiderman Designer Collectible Statue by Unruly Industries
description:
Introducing the Spider-Man Designer Collectible Statue by artist Tracy Tubera, a dynamic and stylish representation of the iconic web-slinger. This officially licensed Marvel collectible, manufactured by Unruly Industries™, captures the essence of Spider-Man's agility and vibrant personality.
Product Details:
 
About the Artist: Tracy Tubera, also known as the ÜBER ILLUSTRATOR SUPREME, combines elements of graffiti, anime, and comic book art in his distinctive style. His artwork is characterized by sharp, crisp line work and vibrant pop colors. Tracy's fusion of pop culture imagery, his love for sneakers, Super Heroes, and humor results in unique and captivating visuals.
Artist Statement: Peter Parker, also known as Spider-Man, is a character that embodies the intersection of sneaker design and comic book art. Like Super Heroes, sneakers have their own secret origins and stories behind their unique designs. Inspired by these shared elements, I created the S.H.S. (Super Heroes in Sneakers) series, which merges two distinct cultures to create visually captivating representations that challenge expectations.
When a quiet, science student from Queens got bitten by a radioactive spider, Peter Parker's life transformed, turning him into the friendly neighborhood Spider-Man. Spider-Man resonated with me at a young age, whether it was his amazing powers, quick wit, or eye-popping design with his iconic red, blue, and black color scheme. After designing Miles Morales and Gwen Stacy, it was only natural to create a Peter Parker art figure, the Spider who inspired the entire Spider-Verse.
For this design, I wanted Peter to be in a classic Spidey pose, showcasing his agility and readiness for action with his hands in the iconic "Ready to THWIP" position. Peter's individualistic style is represented by a pair of sneakers that stand out and are perfectly suited for his swinging through the city. These kicks are foam-cushioned and form-fitting, providing the comfort and flexibility needed for his acrobatic moves. The sneakers match his suit and are complemented by his fresh web-wings.
Embrace the essence of Spider-Man with the Spider-Man Designer Collectible Statue by Tracy Tubera. This visually striking piece combines the iconic imagery of Spider-Man with the vibrant and dynamic style of sneakers, resulting in a must-have collectible for any Marvel fan. Pre-order now to add this extraordinary statue to your collection and showcase the spirit of the friendly neighborhood web-slinger.
Proudly brought to you by Sideshow Collectibles and Superhero Toystore, India's largest and most comprehensive online store for official Marvel Action Figures, Statues, and other Pop-culture merch!

title: Venom Designer Collectible Statue by Unruly Industries
description:
Introducing the Venom Designer Collectible Statue by artist Tracy Tubera, a stunning fusion of symbiotes and amazing sneakers. This officially licensed Marvel collectible, manufactured by Unruly Industries™, showcases the fierce presence of Venom in a unique and captivating design.
Product Details:
About the Artist: Tracy Tubera, also known as the ÜBER ILLUSTRATOR SUPREME, brings a unique mix of graffiti, anime, and comic book art to his creations. His artwork is characterized by sharp, crisp line work and vibrant pop colors. Tracy combines pop culture imagery, his love for sneakers, Super Heroes, and humor to create captivating visuals that are truly his own.
Artist Statement: Eddie, aka Venom, is a character that embodies the fusion of design and colors found in both sneakers and comic books. Just like Super Heroes have their secret origins, sneakers have their own stories behind their unique designs. These vinyl figures, known as S.H.S. (Super Heroes in Sneakers), bring together two distinct cultures to create a visually stunning fusion that challenges expectations.
Born out of hatred and revenge, the alien symbiote bonded with Eddie Brock, creating the new villain, Venom. Venom is big, violent, and scary—a stark contrast to Spider-Man. Designing Eddie AKA Venom allowed me to create the biggest figure I've designed to date, with an overpowering presence. He stands out among my other figures, towering over them with a sinister look and his classic long alien tongue. Eddie needed sneakers that matched his boldness and made a supreme statement, reflecting his alien appearance and his dominance over all.
Embrace the fierce and iconic presence of Venom with the Venom Designer Collectible Statue by Tracy Tubera. This visually stunning piece combines the allure of sneakers with the power of a symbiote, resulting in a unique and captivating representation of the notorious anti-hero. Pre-order now to add this extraordinary collectible to your Marvel collection.
Proudly brought to you by Sideshow Collectibles and Superhero Toystore, India's largest and most comprehensive online store for official Marvel Action Figures, Statues, and other Pop-culture merch!

title: Carnage Designer Collectible Statue by Unruly Industries
description:
Introducing the Carnage Designer Collectible Statue by artist Tracy Tubera, a stunning fusion of killer style and the wrath of the symbiote. This officially licensed Marvel collectible, manufactured by Unruly Industries™, showcases the dynamic presence of Carnage in a unique and captivating design.
Product Details:
 
About the Artist: Tracy Tubera, also known as the ÜBER ILLUSTRATOR SUPREME, brings a unique mix of graffiti, anime, and comic book art to his creations. His artwork is characterized by sharp, crisp line work and vibrant pop colors. Tracy combines pop culture imagery, his love for sneakers, Super Heroes, and humor to create captivating visuals that are truly his own.
Artist Statement: Cletus, aka Carnage, is a character that has always fascinated me. I've always been drawn to the design and colors of sneakers, which is similar to my love for comic books and Super Heroes. Both sneakers and Super Heroes have their own "Secret Origins" that inspired me to explore their commonalities. These vinyl figures, known as S.H.S. (Super Heroes in Sneakers), bring together two distinct cultures to create a visually stunning fusion that challenges expectations.
The spawn of the alien symbiote Venom and the blood of the serial killer Cletus Kasady, Carnage is a deadly villain with a thirst for murder. This new red and black symbiote was created with a single purpose: to kill. Carnage often finds himself in conflict with Spider-Man and Venom, requiring the combined efforts of both heroes to stop his reign of terror. When designing Cletus, I wanted to capture his rage and the symbiote's aggressive nature flowing around him. I aimed to depict Cletus in a moment of madness, ready to strike. His sneakers had to reflect his aggressive and masterful design, representing a cold-blooded killer on the hunt for his prey—Spider-Man and Venom. These three characters are forever connected in a powerful trifecta.
Bring the striking presence of Carnage into your collection with the Carnage Designer Collectible Statue by Tracy Tubera. This visually stunning piece showcases the fusion of sneaker culture and Super Hero aesthetics, resulting in a unique and captivating representation of a cold-blooded killer. Pre-order now to secure your own piece of this incredible design.

title: Old Man Logan 1:10 Scale Statue by Iron Studios
description:
In a potential future in which his enemies have prevailed and most of his allies have perished, an old mutant warrior, unable to let go of his traumatic past, once again starts using his claws in search of revenge and justice, hunting down those responsible for destroying his new life. He decides to eliminate all the villains from the new world and bring peace to Earth.
Over a base of the arid territory known as the Hulkland, the reluctant hero embarks on a mission wearing steel-toed boots, a leather overcoat over his worn-out shirt and denim trousers, and a large hat covering his head. Iron Studios presents their statue "Old Man Logan Wolverine 50th Anniversary Art Scale 1:10", featuring the most popular X-Men superhero in his praised aged alternative version from the story arc of Wolverine from 2008, written by Mark Millar and illustrated by Steve McNiven.
In an alternative universe, the world was conquered by supervillains who divided their territories. The Abomination was later subdued by Hulk, Magneto lost his territory to a new kingpin Dr. Doom, and the Red Skull declared himself President of the United States of Amerika.
The superheroes were almost entirely eliminated, with only a few survivors remaining hidden. Among them, Logan lived with his wife and two sons in a wasteland in old California, controlled by an insane Hulk and his gang formed by his grandchildren. Needing money to pay his rent, Logan accepts a secret package delivery to the capital of New Babylon together with a blind Clint Barton (Hawkeye). After many adventures and challenges, Logan reiterates that his Wolverine persona died in the past when a group of supervillains attacked X-Mansion, and he had to massacre the attackers to ensure the safety of the mutant children.
The entire attack was an illusion created by Mysterio, and his enemies were actually his X-Men companions. That event destroyed Wolverine emotionally and mentally, and he never used his claws again until he returned from this mission and found his family killed by Hulk's gang. Logan finally frees his Adamantium claws, a fictitious indestructible metal, and seeks revenge. The "Old Man Logan" storyline was the main inspiration for the 2017 movie "Logan," starring Hugh Jackman as the main character.
Don't miss your chance to add this Wolverine collectible to your Marvel collectibles collection today!

title: Prince 1:3 Scale Statue by PCS
description:

title: The Flash Movie Batmobile Art Scale by Iron Studios

The Batmobile holds a significant place in Batman's mythology, and this particular version originated from the 1989 movie directed by Tim Burton. Designed by Julian Caldow under the guidance of Tim Burton and Anton Furst, the Batmobile was constructed using a Chevrolet Impala chassis and a Chevy V8 engine, with modifications based on a 1970 Corvette bodywork. Caldow's design incorporated elements from jet aircraft and war machines, resulting in a bolder and darker vehicle that aligned with Burton and Furst's vision for a more menacing Batman.
In "The Flash" movie, Bruce Wayne has retired from his crime-fighting duties in Gotham City. However, in the future, he is sought out by Barry Allen, a metahuman traveler from another Earth. When the threat of General Zod endangers Earth without the presence of Superman or other heroes to stop him, Barry persuades Bruce to come out of retirement and assist in rescuing a captive Kryptonian being.
"The Flash" movie, part of the DC Extended Universe (DCEU), stars Ezra Miller as the speedster hero and brings back 71-year-old actor Michael Keaton in the role of Batman. Iron Studios celebrates this momentous production with their collection of statues inspired by the movie, which includes Batman, two versions of the Flash (including an alternate version portrayed by Ezra Miller), and the iconic Batmobile Deluxe. These statues are available for pre-order now!
Make sure not to miss out on this exciting event and the opportunity to own these remarkable statues inspired by "The Flash" movie.

Dan, on the other hand, is seated casually, legs crossed, slumped over a steaming bowl of noodles. He peers over his shoulder, as if irritated by the interruption of his meal, but not enough to slow down. His portrait is expertly sculpted to depict not only his annoyance but also his clear mouthful of food. His pink gi is sculpted in great detail and is contrasted with his dark brown gloves and rash guard. A pink hair tie matching his gi holds his tight ponytail in place, save for a single strand of hair arcing out from his forehead.
These two martial artists may wear similar uniforms, but their approaches to fighting could not be more different. Kick out the jams and add these two arcade legends to your Street Fighter collection today!

description:

This set of two 1:10 scale collectible statues kicks off the PCS Street Jam line based on the iconic Udon poster showcasing a selection of fan-favorite characters from the Street Fighter franchise.
The first pair of Ryu and Dan represents the two sides of the shotokan coin. Ryu, the stoic disciplinarian, is always searching for a greater challenge to further develop his already impressive skill set. While Dan makes up for his shortcomings with an unyielding confidence and a braggadocious nature that can catch any challenger off guard.
Both figures in this set are fully sculpted - Ryu stands defiantly with his arms crossed, glowering at his next opponent. His earnest expression is carved into his face with a stylized look that mirrors the Street Jam artwork. His classic white gi is sculpted in lifelike detail and complemented by his bright red gloves and headband, with a black belt tied neatly around his waist.
Dan, on the other hand, is seated casually, legs crossed, slumped over a steaming bowl of noodles. He peers over his shoulder, as if irritated by the interruption of his meal, but not enough to slow down. His portrait is expertly sculpted to depict not only his annoyance but also his clear mouthful of food. His pink gi is sculpted in great detail and is contrasted with his dark brown gloves and rash guard. A pink hair tie matching his gi holds his tight ponytail in place, save for a single strand of hair arcing out from his forehead.
These two martial artists may wear similar uniforms, but their approaches to fighting could not be more different. Kick out the jams and add these two arcade legends to your Street Fighter collection today!
